man ls --> man uses by default less command to go through pages with additional shortcuts:
h --> getting help
q --> guit the man pages
Arrowkey up and down --> one line up and down
Enter --> display next line
CTRL+F or Space --> go to next page
CTRL+B --> back to previous page
G --> go to end of the page
g --> go to beginning of the page
/"word" --> search forward for a string
?"word" --> search backwards for a string
n --> takes you to the next match you search for
N --> takes you to the previous match you search for


# checking if a command is shell built-in or executable file (type command)
type rm  --> rm is /usr/bin/rm
type cd  --> cd is a shell builtin
type df  --> shows the path of df command
type apt --> shows the path of apt command


If the command is shell builtin, use the Help command as below:
help cd
help alies

If the command is not a shell builtin or executable files, use the Help as below:
ls --help
rm --help
cd --help


# searching for a command, feature or keyword in all man Pages
man -k ifconfig --> Search and dislay all ifconfig words in man page
man -k uname --> Search and dislay all uname words in man page
man -k "copy files" --> Search and dislay all "copy files" words in man page.

Below commands do the same as above man -k                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                            
apropos ifconfig
apropos uname
apropos "copy files" -- dene bakalım string çalışıyor mu

 
Whatis --> display short description for the command
whatis who
Whatis ls
Whatis rmdir
Whatis pwd
